                            <comment id="13469062" author="jjkoshy" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 01:32:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch overview:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1 - I sent a mail to metrics-user group asking when 3.0.0 will be made&lt;br/&gt;
  available in mvn central. For now, I just did a local build off this:&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/codahale/metrics.git&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/codahale/metrics.git&lt;/a&gt; -&lt;br/&gt;
  10ccc80c0f574f104c4745a1ffa24af0ea92efbf&lt;br/&gt;
  Added metrics-annotation-3.0.0-10ccc80c0.jar&lt;br/&gt;
  metrics-core-3.0.0-10ccc80c0.jar to core/lib (which cannot be included in&lt;br/&gt;
  the diff).&lt;br/&gt;
2 - Made couple of changes due to slight differences in 3.0.0 API.&lt;br/&gt;
3 - Fixed a small bug in the CSV reporter startup.&lt;br/&gt;
4 - Provided a sample config in server.properties.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13469529" author="jjkoshy" created="Thu, 4 Oct 2012 17:29:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I heard back from metrics-user that there is no immediate plan to release 3.0.0, so I think we should move forward with this change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472577" author="nehanarkhede" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 17:35:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Thanks for the patch !&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472768" author="jjkoshy" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 21:29:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review. Committed to 0.8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
